Package: absmaps
Type: Package
Title: A simple way to download, compress and read ABS ASGS data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: person("Will", "Mackey", email = "william.mackey@grattaninstitute.edu.au",
                role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Will Mackey <william.mackey@grattaninstitute.edu.au>
License: GPL-3
Description: This package allows the user to download and compress (as desired) spatial data from the Australian Statistical Geography Standard (ASGS). The spatial data can then be loaded as an easy-to-use `sf` object and combined with information to be mapped using ggplot2's `geom_sf`.
Depends: R (>= 3.1)
Imports:
    readr,
    sf,
    rmapshaper,
    curl
Suggests:
	knitr, 
	rmarkdown,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
